com.opengamma.strata.collect.id

Class StandardLink<T extends IdentifiableBean>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.collect.id.StandardLink<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the target
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Link<T>, Resolvable<StandardLink<T>>, StandardIdentifiable, Serializable, Bean, ImmutableBean

    public final class StandardLink<T extends IdentifiableBean>
extends Object
implements Link<T>, Resolvable<StandardLink<T>>, StandardIdentifiable, ImmutableBean, Serializable
    Standard implementation of a link to a target object using an identifier.

    A link provides loose coupling between different parts of the object model. For example, an equity trade can hold a link to the underlying equity. The two objects can be updated independently of each other. If the link resolver supports historic versions, then the correct version of the target will be returned when resolved. The target object should be immutable to ensure the safety of the link.

    A link can be in one of two states, resolvable and resolved.

    In the resolvable state, the link contains the identifier and type of the target object. The target can only be obtained using a LinkResolver.

    In the resolved state, the link directly embeds the target object.

    Links are expected to be resolvable. It is reasonable to expect that when resolve(LinkResolver) is called, the target of the link is available. For this reason, if the target is not found, a LinkResolutionException will be thrown.

    This is the standard implementation of Link. It is suitable for all link targets except those that have generic parameters.

      • resolvable

        public static <R extends IdentifiableBean> StandardLink<R> resolvable(StandardId identifier,
                                                                      Class<R> targetType)
        Create a resolvable link for the specified identifier and type.

        The returned link will be in the resolvable state, containing the identifier and type. When the resolve(LinkResolver) method is called, the resolver will be used to find the target, for example from a database.

        The type is expressed as a standard Class object.

        Type Parameters:
        R - the type of the link
        Parameters:
        identifier - the primary identifier of the target
        targetType - the type of the target
        Returns:
        a new resolvable link

      • resolved

        public static <R extends IdentifiableBean> StandardLink<R> resolved(R target)
        Create a link with the link target embedded directly.

        The returned link will be in the resolved state, directly embedding the target object. When the resolve(LinkResolver) method is called, the embedded target will be returned without needing to use the resolver.

        Type Parameters:
        R - the type of the link
        Parameters:
        target - the link target
        Returns:
        a new resolved link

      • resolve

        public T resolve(LinkResolver resolver)
        Resolves this link using the specified resolver.

        The resolver is used to find the linked target. In the resolvable state, the resolver is used to find the target, throwing an exception of the target cannot be found. In the resolved state, the directly embedded target is returned, without using the resolver.

        The returned target may contain other unresolved links.

        Specified by:
        resolve in interface Link<T extends IdentifiableBean>
        Parameters:
        resolver - the resolver to use for the resolution
        Returns:
        the target
        Throws:
        LinkResolutionException - if the target cannot be resolved

      • resolveLinks

        public StandardLink<T> resolveLinks(LinkResolver resolver)
        Resolves this link, and any links that the target contains, using the specified resolver.

        First, the target is resolved using resolve(LinkResolver). Second, if the target implements Resolvable, it is resolved as well. The result is wrapped using resolved(IdentifiableBean). The returned target should not contain any unresolved links.

        Specified by:
        resolveLinks in interface Resolvable<StandardLink<T extends IdentifiableBean>>
        Parameters:
        resolver - the resolver to use for the resolution
        Returns:
        the fully resolved link
        Throws:
        LinkResolutionException - if a link cannot be resolved
